<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF2C6A93FF8491D21AB7BC86" box="[120,1207,1931,1972]" pageId="215" pageNumber="977" type="activity">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF2C6A93FF8491D21AB7BC86" blockId="215.[120,1331,1501,2283]" box="[120,1207,1931,1972]" pageId="215" pageNumber="977">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFF2C6A93FF8491D21F64BC9F" bold="true" box="[120,356,1931,1965]" pageId="215" pageNumber="977">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
A colony of Bokhara 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF2C6A93FD6591D61CF3BC82" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[665,755,1935,1968]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="215" pageNumber="977" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
roosted in an abandoned mine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF2C6A93FF8591EB1ACBB330" pageId="215" pageNumber="977" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF2C6A93FF8591EB1ACBB330" blockId="215.[120,1331,1501,2283]" pageId="215" pageNumber="977">
